What is RDD?
What is Dataframe?

What is Partitions?

To all every executor to perform work in parallel, Spark breaks up the data 
into chunks called partitions.
An important thing to note is that DataFrames you do not manipulate partitions
manually or individually. 

What is transformation?
What is action?
Action instructs Spark to compute a result from a series of transformation.
there are 3 kinds of actionss:
1. to view data in the console
2. to collect data to native objects in the respective language.
3. to write to output data sources.

What is the difference between col and column function

if you need to refer specific dataframe column, you can use the col method on the
specific dataframe.


